ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I have felt cheerful and in good spirits
Notes: -9 = Not in wave; -8 = Out-of-range; -7 Not applicable; -6 = Logical skip; -5 Not asked (not in version of survey); -4 = Multiple answers; -3 = Missing (due to technical error); -2 = Do not know; -1 = Refuse; 0 = At no time; 1 = Some of the time; 2 = Less than half the time; 3 = More than half the time; 4 = Most of the time; 5 = All of the time

ElementDescription: Total score
Notes: -9 = Not in wave; -8 = Out-of-range; -7 Not applicable; -6 = Logical skip; -5 Not asked (not in version of survey); -4 = Multiple answers; -3 = Missing (due to technical error); -2 = Do not know; -1 = Refuse; 0 = Worst possible quality of life; 25 = Best possible quality of life; 999 = Cannot be determined if not all questions answered

ElementDescription: Percentage score - Multiply total x4
Notes: -9 = Not in wave; -8 = Out-of-range; -7 Not applicable; -6 = Logical skip; -5 Not asked (not in version of survey); -4 = Multiple answers; -3 = Missing (due to technical error); -2 = Do not know; -1 = Refuse; 0=Worst possible quality of life; 100=Best possible quality of life

ElementDescription: Valid Total
The platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
Date script was run
time script was started
Assigned group ID number
session ID/screening ID
Time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
Whether script was completed
Notes: 0 = Script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 1 = Script was completed (all conditions run)

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Treatment arm
